<h1>In this role, you'll get to:</h1>

<ul>
  <li>Build things that drive business value and make an impact</li>
  <li>Explore new technologies and figure out where to use them</li>
  <li>Come up with creative ideas for projects and work through them with your teammates</li>
  <li>Lead multiple projects with many moving parts</li>
  <li>Set high standards for yourself and challenge those around you to do the same</li>
</ul>

<h2>We need your help to:</h2>

<ul>
  <li>Head our development team</li>
  <li>Build / maintain Websites using static or server-side React configuration
  <li>Build / maintain design system</li>
  <li>Develop landing pages, emails, and other reusable templates using internal design system</li>
  <li>Work with designers to review and ensure the feasibility of website designs and inline with our design system</li>
  <li>Contribute to the creation of internal libraries, reusable resources, and processes</li>
  <li>Proactively identify opportunities to improve performance of client websites</li>
  <li>Assisting customers to integrate their marketing tools inc. marketing website</li>
  <li>Own the development backlog and be comfortable prioritising and managing your development team's time, ensuring all projects are completed on time.</li>
  <li>Support Junior team member in building and maintaining Websites in HubSpot
</ul>


<h3>We are looking for a legend with:</h3>

<ul> 
  <li>4+ years commercial web development experience</li>
  <li>Attention to detail is your stick</li>
  <li>CMS Experience super important</li>
  <li>Strong understanding of HTML5, CSS3, Javascript and cross-browser compatibility</li>
  <li>Experience using CSS preprocessors such as SCSS or LESS</li>
  <li>Experience with React, Gatsby and NextJS</li>
  <li>Experience with utility CSS frameworks such as Tailwind or BassCSS</li>
  <li>Understanding of and an interest in UX principles</li>
  <li>Experience with version control in a team setting</li>
  <li>The development team partners closely with the design and strategy teams, so we look for comfort building relationships and influencing</li>
  <li>Experience working in an agile environment</li>
  <li>We use Asana, Notion, and Slack to coordinate work between teams</li>
  <li>Comfortable working in an agency environment</li>
  <li>Working on different clients at the same time</li>
  <li>Project deadlines</li>
  <li>Motivated to mentor other dev team members</li>
</ul>

